        "old_string": "/**\n * A record batch is a container for records. In old versions of the record format (versions 0 and 1),\n * a batch consisted always of a single record if no compression was enabled, but could contain\n * many records otherwise. Newer versions (magic versions 2 and above) will generally contain many records\n * regardless of compression.\n */\npublic interface RecordBatch extends Iterable<Record> {",
        "new_string": "/**\n * A record batch is a container for records in the Kafka protocol. In older record format versions\n * (magic 0 and 1), a batch contained a single record if uncompressed, but could contain many records\n * with compression. Newer versions (magic 2 and above) typically contain multiple records regardless\n * of compression configuration.\n *\n * <p><strong>Thread Safety:</strong> Implementations of this interface are <em>not thread-safe</em>.\n * External synchronization is required if accessed concurrently.</p>\n *\n * <p><strong>Protocol Role:</strong> RecordBatch is the fundamental serialization unit in Kafka's\n * log segment files. Each batch contains a binary-encoded header with metadata (offsets, timestamps,\n * producer information, attributes), followed by compressed or uncompressed record data. The batch\n * header includes CRC-32C checksum validation to detect corruption.</p>\n *\n * <p><strong>Format Versions:</strong> The interface abstracts over multiple magic versions:\n * <ul>\n *   <li>Magic v0: Simple format with checksum, no timestamps or producer info</li>\n *   <li>Magic v1: Adds timestamp support</li>\n *   <li>Magic v2: Introduces producer ID/epoch, sequence numbers, and improved transaction support</li>\n * </ul>\n * </p>\n *\n * <p><strong>Key Invariants:</strong>\n * <ul>\n *   <li>Batch offsets are monotonically increasing across the log</li>\n *   <li>For magic v2+, the base and last offsets from the original batch are preserved through\n *       log compaction to maintain producer state</li>\n *   <li>Checksums cover batch attributes and records (magic byte position varies)</li>\n * </ul>\n * </p>\n *\n * @see DefaultRecordBatch\n * @see MemoryRecords\n * @see CompressionType\n * @see TimestampType\n */\npublic interface RecordBatch extends Iterable<Record> {",
        "replace_all": false
      },
